headline: Coca-Cola’s Week in Review: Analysts Raise Price Targets Q4 Beat
summary: Coca-Cola (NYSE:KO) closed Friday at $78.67, down 0.5% for the week but up 12.5% year-to-date. That crushes both the SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (NYSEARCA:SPY) (flat YTD) and is close to the Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund (NYSEARCA:XLP) (up 15.2% YTD).
